One lost 4chan-y cultural concept/terminology is NOPE/noping, like quickly exiting a situation due to perceived danger. E.g. You're walking alone at night and hear a weird animal noise from nearby bushes or see some silhouettes and you run away so you say "I noped out of there".

Another lost terminology from early 2000s computer programming circles is the concept of the "power user", someone who pushes a certain software to its limits and is very competent/skilled and good at getting the most out of it. A lot of us here are basically twitter power users.

It's obviously meant for computers but for example a gym membership power user would be someone who goes every day of the week, uses the bodybuilding machine selection and then the Crossfit area for cleans and always hits the sauna too. Gets the most out of his money. Power user.
